This project uses 2 licenses:

1. The demo's source code (script files, scene files, shaders, and generally all Godot-generated resources) is available under the MIT license.
2. Art assets (image textures and 3D models) are [CC BY-NC-SA 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/).

In short, this means you can reuse and adapt code freely, including in commercial projects, as long as you give credit to GDQuest. Art assets can be shared and adapted freely as long as you give credit, do not use them for commercial purposes, and distribute any derivative works under the same license.

For assets, you can add this to your credits: "Additional assets CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 GDQuest (https://www.gdquest.com/)".

For code, you can add this to your credits: "Portions of this project use code from GDQuest (https://www.gdquest.com/) licensed under MIT".

It really helps when you credit creators, so thank you in advance!

The above is just for clarity. You can find the exact terms of each license below.

